From 975566cc7408d1af1b6f2037900bd28070e3d384 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <faisalkhan91@outlook.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 21:12:41 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(csp): unbreak prerendered blog first paint and lock
 down with regression checks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Beasties (Angular's critical-CSS inliner) emits a deferred stylesheet via
`<link media="print" onload="this.media='all'">`. Our strict CSP had no
`'unsafe-hashes'`, so the inline `onload` was silently dropped — the
stylesheet stayed at `media="print"` and prerendered blog pages rendered
unstyled on first paint. Reload masked the bug because the Angular SW
served the cached `/index.html` shell (no Beasties pattern) instead of
the prerendered route.

The Angular SW also intercepted Google Fonts via `dataGroups.google-fonts`
and the cross-origin fetch failed on first install behind Cloudflare
Tunnel, leaving fonts unstyled until a refresh.

Fix
- Self-host fonts via @fontsource/{inter,poppins,fira-code,space-grotesk};
  bundled @font-face rules ship in styles-*.css with no third-party
  dependency. Removes the `google-fonts` SW dataGroup and drops the
  `https://fonts.{googleapis,gstatic}.com` entries from the CSP.
- Allow exactly the literal `this.media='all'` Beasties handler via
  `'unsafe-hashes' 'sha256-MhtPZXr7+LpJUY5qtMutB+qWfQtMaPccfe7QXtCcEYc='`
  in `script-src` (mirrored in security-headers.conf and build-csp.mjs).
- Allow the Cloudflare Insights beacon: `https://static.cloudflareinsights.com`
  in `script-src`, `https://cloudflareinsights.com` in `connect-src`.

Regression checks (so this class of bug fails CI, not users)
- scripts/audit-csp.mjs hashes every inline event handler and inline
  `<script>` in dist/ HTML and asserts each is covered by the generated
  script-src; chained at the end of `build:prod`.
- tests/e2e/csp.spec.ts injects the prod CSP via page.route() onto every
  document response and asserts zero CSP-shaped console errors /
  pageerrors across all PRERENDERED_ROUTES.
- tests/smoke/prod-csp-probe.mjs + new csp-probe job in smoke.yml hit
  the live URL daily and catch edge-injected scripts (Cloudflare
  Insights variants, Rocket Loader, etc.) the offline build can't see.

Other
- npm update for in-range Angular 21.2.11 / @angular/build 21.2.9 /
  eslint 10.3 / jsdom 29.1 / axe 4.11.3 patch bumps.
- Drop the now-stale typescript major-bump ignore in dependabot.yml
  (Angular 21.2.x peer is `>=5.9 <6.1`, so TS 6 is in range).

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
