From 08158b714d9f2766c6273645047adf423ffd28e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 22:19:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(theme): add multi-theme registry with palette picker
 and last-by-scheme toggle
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Expand the binary dark/light system into a typed registry of six themes
(crimson-dark, crimson-light, one-dark, tokyo-night, catppuccin-mocha,
solarized-light) discoverable from the existing command palette, while
keeping SSR-safe pre-paint, strict CSP, and the existing toggle ergonomic.

Registry as the single source of truth
- src/app/core/services/theme.registry.ts: ThemeId union, ThemeDef shape
  ({ id, label, scheme, swatch, metaThemeColor }), THEME_REGISTRY array,
  DEFAULT_DARK_ID / DEFAULT_LIGHT_ID, isThemeId guard, getThemeDef lookup.
- theme.registry.spec.ts pins the registry shape AND parses the inline
  pre-paint script in src/index.html, asserting its allowlist matches the
  registry one-for-one. Drift between the two (the most painful failure
  mode — silently-wrong theme on first paint) now fails unit tests
  before it ever reaches a CSP surprise.

Service refactor (theme.service.ts)
- setTheme(id) is the new write path: validates against the registry,
  persists to localStorage, updates <html data-theme>, syncs every
  <meta name="theme-color">, and runs inside document.startViewTransition
  when available (preserved from before).
- toggle() is now last-by-scheme: tracks the most recently chosen dark
  AND most recently chosen light id, so toggling from tokyo-night → light
  → dark returns to tokyo-night, not crimson-dark. Defaults fall back to
  DEFAULT_{DARK,LIGHT}_ID.
- Legacy 'dark'/'light' localStorage values migrate to crimson-dark /
  crimson-light on first read.
- themeDef() signal exposes the full ThemeDef so consumers don't have to
  re-resolve via the registry.

CSP-safe pre-paint script (src/index.html)
- The synchronous boot script now reads localStorage, validates against
  an inline THEME_IDS allowlist (mirroring the registry), migrates
  legacy values, and otherwise picks DEFAULT_{LIGHT,DARK}_ID via
  matchMedia. data-theme is unconditionally set so CSS tokens always
  resolve on first paint — no FOUC across themes or schemes.
- Recomputed SHA-256 ('sha256-puKWb5LlVuesXkmqJEK8DuseZjDq32KBLKuYwdDa9EI=')
  and updated security-headers.conf. The prod build's scripts/build-csp.mjs
  rehashes from dist/ automatically, and audit-csp catches drift.

Theme tokens + highlight.js (src/styles.css)
- Renamed [data-theme='light'] → [data-theme='crimson-light'] so the new
  naming convention is consistent.
- Added four new [data-theme='...'] token blocks (One Dark, Tokyo Night,
  Catppuccin Mocha, Solarized Light) covering the full surface/text/
  brand/accent/border surface contract.
- Added matching per-theme highlight.js overrides so code blocks read
  natively against each palette instead of falling back to the dark
  defaults.

Command palette as the discovery surface
- CommandItem is now { kind: 'route' | 'action', ..., swatch?, run?() }.
  Theme entries are appended to the catalog with kind:'action' that calls
  themeService.setTheme(id). select() branches on kind.
- openWith(initialQuery) lets external triggers open the palette
  pre-filtered (e.g. 'theme:').
- Renders a 10px palette-swatch dot for theme rows so the picker reads
  visually, not just textually.

Sidebar + shell wiring
- Sidebar's single isDark input is replaced by currentTheme: ThemeDef
  (signal-driven from themeService.themeDef()). The toggle button
  becomes a compound theme-toggle-group: a primary toggle button +
  a chevron theme-picker-btn. Plain click toggles by scheme; Shift/Alt
  click — or the chevron — emits themePickerRequested, which the shell
  forwards to palette.openWith('theme:').
- The mobile FAB gets the same affordance via onMobileThemeClick.
- icons.ts gains a 'palette' icon for the picker control.
- Shell holds a viewChild.required<CommandPaletteComponent> reference
  so it can drive openWith() from the sidebar/FAB outputs.

Mermaid theme detection fix (blog-post.component.ts)
- Diagrams now read the active scheme from ThemeService instead of
  inferring from a stale boolean, so mermaid renders against the
  correct palette across all six themes (not just dark/light).

Tests
- theme.service.spec.ts: registry, legacy migration, setTheme side-
  effects, last-by-scheme toggle round-trip, SSR safety,
  meta theme-color sync.
- sidebar.component.spec.ts: currentTheme input, themeToggled vs.
  themePickerRequested outputs, icon aria-label assertions
  (Angular [name] is a property binding, not a DOM attribute).
- shell.component.spec.ts: mobile FAB aria-label, plain vs Shift+click,
  themePickerRequested → palette().openWith() round-trip.
- command-palette.component.spec.ts: theme actions in catalog,
  openWith() seeding, swatch rendering (rgb() normalisation),
  ArrowDown navigation across the full catalog.
- tests/e2e/theme.spec.ts: pre-paint applies seeded id, legacy
  'dark'/'light' migrate, any registry id is honoured, the inline
  script lives in <head>, and Cmd+K → 'tokyo' → Enter swaps
  data-theme + storage + meta theme-color.
- tests/e2e/visual.spec.ts: existing crimson dark/light snapshots
  preserved; gated VISUAL_REGRESSION=1 loop adds hero-only snapshots
  for the four new themes.

Verified
- npm run build:prod passes (audit-csp: 67 inline-script hashes,
